===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – a mouth full of teeth. Now {{liushu|psc|nocap=y}} with phonetic {{och-l|止}} added.

===Etymology===
Unclear. Not related to [[w:Tibetan language|Tibetan]] {{m|bo|མཆེ་བ||fang, tusk}}, which is cognate with {{m|zh|齻||eyetooth}}, but may be the same word as {{cog|zhx-min-pro|*kʰiᴮ||tooth}}. Another possibility is a derivation from an Austroasiatic etymon; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}} (p.188) suggests a possible relationship to {{cog|km|ខ្នាយ||tusk, spur}}, as Austroasiatic medial /n/ is often deleted in loans.

